  <body>
    <header><para styleclass="Heading1">SCSI Devices</para></header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The SRM console exposes SCSI-related variables (<text styleclass="Code Example">scsi_poll</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">scsi_reset</text>), but EmulatR does not currently model a SCSI host adapter. [TODO: confirm -- SCSI is not implemented; treat as planned.] The <text styleclass="Code Example">VirtualScsiDevice</text> endpoint class exists in the device library for the eventual <text styleclass="Code Example">dka</text> path.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">For reference, the DEC RZ-series drives a DS10-class machine would address over SCSI (all 512-byte blocks):</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
